11 the time of inspection.
12 F. Nothing in this act shall prevent the State Fire Marshal
13 from enforcing the minimum code requirements as allowed by law and
14 revoking the operations of a mobile food preparation vehicle upon
15 cause when it is determined to be inherently dangerous to the
16 health, safety, or welfare of persons within the State of Oklahoma.
17 G. Nothing in this act shall prevent a political subdivision
18 from enforcing the political subdivision's event permits,
19 operational fees, land use regulations, zoning, and other ordinances
20 in relation to the operation of a mobile food preparation vehicle
21 within the boundaries of said political subdivision.
